    "The activation function uses a rectified linear unit (ReLU) in the first three hidden layers and a linear function in the last layer.",
    "The mean square error (MSE) is used as the error function.",
    "The final results of all the four models are used to assess the confidence indicators for each of the three available outcomes.",
    "In Predictive-DQN, Bitcoin-related tweets are utilized to extract sentiments, thereby separating them into positive (compound score between 0 and 1), neutral (score of 0), and negative (score between 0 and -1) categories as described above.",
    "In leveraging these sentiment scores and employing the DQN algorithm, the objective is to construct a model capable of predicting future Bitcoin prices."
